  "campus_description": "OXF@OXFORD",
  "course_description": "A side-car course brings together a subset of students from two courses that overlap in methodologies, topics, etc., to create a short interdisciplinary course that runs simultaneously with its two sponsoring courses. One credit, S/U only. Schedule and format arranged by sponsoring professors.",
  "course_notes": "Title: Gut Check: Science Communication, Literacy, and the Microbes of Cancer We plan to spotlight diverse groups of scientists and explore their current research including excerpts of primary literature. We intend to tie this into the purpose and perception of science communication at different levels (from primary article to news and social media). Our teaching team expertise spans the fields of Cancer Biology (Dr. Silva) Microbiology (Dr. Essler), and Science, Writing & Communication (Dr. Reid). This class will meet on the following dates: 8/28, 9/4, 9/18, 10/2, 10/16, 10/30, 11/13.",
  "requisites": "QTM 100 or QTM_OX 100 or BUS 350 or BUS_OX 350 or equivalent transfer credit as prerequisite.",
